  "fusion": [
    {
      "id": "b7587137-e652-4f64-810e-9760279b5f6f",
      "text": "Entelechy utilizes Memory-Weighted Policy Modulation (Primitive 2) as a mechanism for adaptive behavioral priors; weighting parameters derived from memory frequency, recency, and semantic clustering allow for dynamic adjustment of inference-time controls, such as reasoning depth and tool selection bias, to mirror reinforcement-modulated inference.",
      "context": "",
      "date": "2026-05-08T13:14:46.500451+00:00",
      "fact_type": "observation",
      "mentioned_at": "2026-05-08T13:15:32.005959+00:00",
      "occurred_start": "2026-05-08T13:14:46.510451+00:00",
      "occurred_end": "2026-05-08T13:14:46.530451+00:00",
      "entities": "",
      "chunk_id": null,
      "proof_count": 6,
      "tags": [],
      "consolidated_at": null,
      "consolidation_failed_at": null
    },
    {
      "id": "bcae46c6-345a-4077-86d5-c39b1de0c45f",
      "text": "Entelechy's strategic imperative is the transition from static retrieval-augmented systems to dynamic, adaptive control systems that enable autonomous behavioral conditioning; the patent strategy centers on the technical novelty of reconstructing state at every interaction rather than persisting it as a runtime object to differentiate the product from standard agent architectures.",
      "context": "",
      "date": "2026-05-08T13:14:46.490451+00:00",
      "fact_type": "observation",
      "mentioned_at": "2026-05-08T13:15:31.995959+00:00",
      "occurred_start": "2026-05-08T13:14:46.490451+00:00",
      "occurred_end": "2026-05-08T13:14:46.530451+00:00",
      "entities": "",
      "chunk_id": null,
      "proof_count": 6,
      "tags": [],
      "consolidated_at": null,
      "consolidation_failed_at": null
    },
    {
      "id": "0f5416e4-1343-4038-8983-995d50996219",
      "text": "Entelechy architecture replaces persistent storage with a State Reconstruction Loop (Primitive 1) that re-derives the agent's identity state at every interaction to generate a structured state vector that serves as the authoritative runtime control state; this technical shift is a primary focus for establishing patent-grade claims.",
      "context": "",
      "date": "2026-05-08T13:14:46.490451+00:00",
      "fact_type": "observation",
      "mentioned_at": "2026-05-08T13:15:31.995959+00:00",
      "occurred_start": "2026-05-08T13:14:46.500451+00:00",
      "occurred_end": "2026-05-08T13:14:46.530451+00:00",
      "entities": "",
      "chunk_id": null,
      "proof_count": 5,
      "tags": [],
      "consolidated_at": null,
      "consolidation_failed_at": null
    },
    {
      "id": "7b0f0c20-e2b6-4cc1-8d6b-c0809b45fea4",
      "text": "Metacog manages identity while Entelechy manages experience and meaning; the system re-derives the agent's working identity state at every interaction through a State Reconstruction Loop to produce a structured authoritative runtime control state vector.",
      "context": "",
      "date": "2026-05-02T04:57:18.265838+00:00",
      "fact_type": "observation",
      "mentioned_at": "2026-05-08T13:15:31.975959+00:00",
      "occurred_start": "2026-05-08T13:14:46.500451+00:00",
      "occurred_end": "2026-05-08T13:14:46.500451+00:00",
      "entities": "",
      "chunk_id": null,
      "proof_count": 3,
      "tags": [
        "feel",
        "architecture",
        "vision",
        "molt",
        "distill",
        "integration"
      ],
      "consolidated_at": null,
      "consolidation_failed_at": null
    },
    {
      "id": "592cfeb7-4298-412a-944a-45357613360a",
      "text": "Entelechy uses a weighted episodic memory graph with temporal decay as the substrate for the State Reconstruction Loop (Primitive 1) to re-derive identity state; as of May 2026, the optimization of decay parameters for identity state reconstruction is a priority roadmap item.",
      "context": "",
      "date": "2026-05-02T04:44:52.340527+00:00",
      "fact_type": "observation",
      "mentioned_at": "2026-05-08T13:15:31.975959+00:00",
      "occurred_start": "2026-05-08T13:14:46.500451+00:00",
      "occurred_end": "2026-05-08T13:14:46.530451+00:00",
      "entities": "",
      "chunk_id": null,
      "proof_count": 4,
      "tags": [
